sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1638038
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Yhbj fused to T25 domain of CyaA with cAMP-induced RFP reporter
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The RNase adapter protein YhbJ fused to the T25-domain of the adenylate cyclase, CyaA, from Bordetella pertussis. This construct can be used in the two-hybrid screening of protein-protein interactions between YhbJ and another x protein fused to the T18 domain. If a random set of peptide aptamers is conjugated to the T18-domain, one can screen for specific peptide aptamers against YhbJ.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Jens Sivk??r Pettersen

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K118011
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the promoter for the ''Eschaerichia coli'' JM109 ''cstA'' gene. It includes the CRP-binding site and the RNA polymerase-binding site. Low glucose concentration results in increased activity by adenylate cyclase. cAMP binds to the cAMP receptor protein, which, in its bound form, is able to associate with the promoter and promote transcription of the downstream gene. (''cstA'' encodes the carbon starvation protein.)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Andrew Hall

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1638003
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: T25 domain of cyaA from Bordetella pertussis (IPTG inducible)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The T25 domain of CyaA to be used in the bacterial two-hybrid system. The expression of the gene is under control of a lac operator and is induced by IPTG. When protein-coding genes is suffixed to the T25 and T18 domains of the bacterial two-hybrid system, the interaction of these two proteins can be examined. If the protein associates, T25 and T18 associates too, and convert ATP to cAMP.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Jens Sivk??r Pettersen

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0034
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix.

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info for this part: Brian Chow
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Derived from the TE terminator of T7 bacteriophage between Genes 1.3 and 1.4 <genbank>V01146</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcription terminator for the E.coli RNA polymerase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Suggested by Sri Kosuri and Drew Endy as a high efficiency terminator. The 5' end cutoff was placed immediately after the TAA stop codon and the 3' end cutoff was placed just prior to the RBS of Gene 1.4 (before AAGGAG).

Use anywhere transcription should be stopped when the gene of interest is upstream of this terminator.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0010
